analysis.interpretation: 5-qubit GHZ via Qiskit transpiler routing: 86.0% fidelity. Same qubit set as AI ([5,2,4,6,8] vs [2,4,5,6,8]) but valid CNOT chain. AI circuit used invalid pairs (q4-q5, q5-q6 not connected).

ai_routing.note: Used invalid CNOT pairs (q4-q5, q5-q6). Succeeded once (hardware auto-routing?) but FAILED on re-submission (job 415436). Non-reproducible.

qiskit_routing.note: Valid CNOT chain through all connected pairs. Deterministic across 20 transpiler seeds.

comparison.conclusion: Qiskit transpiler achieves same fidelity as AI routing (86.0% vs 86.7%) with valid circuits. For 3-qubit GHZ, AI and Qiskit choose identical routing [2,4,6]. The AI adds no measurable routing advantage over Qiskit optimization_level=3 when given the same topology/error data.
